1. Trump's involvement in cryptocurrencies makes legislation "more complicated", but the stablecoin and market structure bill is still expected to be passed before August;
2. The US has adjusted the additional tariffs on China at 00:01 am on May 14, Eastern Time;
3. Sources: The United States does not seek a depreciation of the dollar in tariff negotiations;
4. Director of the US Digital Assets Committee: It is unfair to question the Trump family's involvement in the crypto industry;
5. The US CFTC issued a statement: Commissioner Summer Mersinger will resign;
6. Wintermute will set up its US headquarters in New York and appoint Ron Hammond as policy director;
7. Thumzup: Will use Coinbase Prime as a Bitcoin custodian and prime broker;
8. The Thai Ministry of Finance plans to issue $150 million in digital investment tokens G-Token;
9. Analyst: Robinhood's acquisition of WonderFi for $179 million may increase revenue by 10%;
10. Chainlink and JPMorgan Chase's Kinexys and Ondo Finance Launch bank payment channels to the token asset market;
11. The French Interior Minister plans to hold a crypto industry security meeting to respond to the recent kidnapping incidents;
12. Analyst: Bitcoin's weekly MACD trend indicates that bullish momentum has been strengthened again.
